    <h1>Make Washing Soda/Soda Ash from Baking Soda (for fabric scouring and more)</h1>
    <hr>
    <p>Washing soda, also known as soda ash, is used in our household to scour fabrics in preparation for waxing and indigo dying, to clean laundry, the kitchen and the bathroom, and to remove stains from stainless steel cookware. It is a very versatile natural ingredient but is not as easily available as baking soda, so we will show you how we make washing soda from baking soda. Enjoy this easy tutorial!</p>
